Optimizers in Deep Learning

Optimizer means:

"Method used to update weights and reduce errors."

After every prediction:

Loss function calculates error
Optimizer corrects weights

Different optimizers use different techniques to learn faster and better.

========================================

1️⃣ SGD (Stochastic Gradient Descent)

Full Name:

Stochastic Gradient Descent

Works:

Updates weights little by little

================

Simple idea:

Wrong Prediction
      ↓
Small Correction
      ↓
Repeat Again

==================

Advantages

✅ Simple
✅ Uses less memory

Disadvantages

❌ Slow learning
❌ Can get stuck

Real-time Example

Like:

Climbing down a hill step by step slowly.

2️⃣ RMSprop

Full Name:

Root Mean Square Propagation

Works:

Adjusts learning speed automatically
Advantages

✅ Faster than SGD
✅ Good for deep learning

Disadvantages

❌ Slightly complex

Real-time Example

Like:

Walking slowly on rough road and faster on smooth road.

3️⃣ Adam

Full Name:

Adaptive Moment Estimation

Combination of:

Momentum
RMSprop

Most popular optimizer.

Advantages

✅ Fast
✅ Smart learning
✅ Works well in most problems

Disadvantages

❌ Uses more memory

Real-time Example

Like:

Smart teacher correcting mistakes efficiently.

4️⃣ AdamW

Improved version of Adam.

Extra feature:

Prevents overfitting better

"W" means:

Weight Decay
Advantages

✅ Better generalization
✅ Used in Transformers, LLMs

Real-time Example

Like:

Strict teacher preventing bad habits.

5️⃣ Adadelta

Works:

Automatically changes learning rate
Advantages

✅ No need manual learning rate tuning

Disadvantages

❌ Sometimes slower

Real-time Example

Like:

Automatic bike gear adjustment.

6️⃣ Adagrad

Works:

Gives different learning rates for different weights

Good for:

Sparse data
NLP tasks
Advantages

✅ Good for text data

Disadvantages

❌ Learning becomes very slow later

Real-time Example

Like:

Paying more attention to weak subjects.

7️⃣ Adamax

Variant of Adam based on infinity norm.

Advantages

✅ Stable for some datasets

Disadvantages

❌ Less commonly used

Real-time Example

Like:

Stronger version of Adam for extreme situations.

8️⃣ Adafactor

Memory-efficient optimizer.

Mostly used in:

Large Language Models
Transformers
Advantages

✅ Uses less memory
✅ Good for huge models

Disadvantages

❌ Complex

Real-time Example

Like:

Compact storage system for large companies.

9️⃣ Nadam

Combination of:

Adam
Nesterov Momentum
Advantages

✅ Faster convergence
✅ Smooth learning

Disadvantages

❌ More calculations

Real-time Example

Like:

Predicting next step before moving.

🔟 Ftrl

Full Name:

Follow The Regularized Leader

Mostly used in:

Recommendation systems
Ads systems
Advantages

✅ Works well with huge sparse data

Disadvantages

❌ Not common for image tasks

Real-time Example

Like:

Online shopping recommendation engine.

